System
Main
System
Adiabatic air humidification systems are designed to provide optimal humidity levels without the need for heating the water. This not only maximizes energy efficiency but also minimizes the need for regular maintenance. By utilizing atomizing nozzles with various orifice diameters, such as 85 µm (0.3 GPH), 2x85 µm (0.6 GPH), or 200 µm (0.9 GPH), water is transformed into a fine fog under high pressure. This mist instantly evaporates, ensuring that it doesn't accumulate on surfaces like floors, furniture, or equipment. These advanced systems are suitable for residential and office spaces. Furthermore, each system is equipped with a preliminary water purification and softening module to ensure long-lasting operation of the central module and fogging nozzles, while also promoting the safety and purity of the sprayed water.

The water treatment and pump units are conveniently located in a suitable utility area, making them easily accessible for maintenance. High-pressure tubes and fogging nozzles are discreetly positioned behind walls or ceilings, allowing for an unobtrusive installation. Additionally, these systems offer the ability to independently set the desired humidity level in each room through specially designed regulators.
Currently, Buhler-AHS offers three series of adiabatic air humidification systems: Playgreen, Manitoba, and Superior. Each series differs in capacity, measured by the amount of fogged water (GPH), and the number of humidification zones (simultaneously activated groups of nozzles). Choose from the 2-zone Playgreen, the 10-zone Manitoba, or the premium 10-zone Superior based on your specific requirements.

Key technical advantages of the system include:
Amulti stage filtration process that demineralized water by 97-99% (99.5% for Superior 18), akin to distilled water. This is achieved through the softener (optional), mechanical microfilter, carbon filter, and RO filter (2-stage for Superior 18).
Furthermore, an additional deionization module supplies fully purified water with a low conductivity level of 0.1 µS/cm.
The built-in 2-stage UV decontaminator ensures that the water is sterilized, providing peace of mind (continuous extensive UV sterilization for Superior 18)
Depending on the type, each nozzle can effectively cover an area ranging from 100 to 1,500 sq ft.

MORE ABOUT OUR SYSTEM
Play green 6 is a standard capacity system with a 2-zone capability and a PG6UV unit, boasting a throughput of 1.6 gallons per hour (6 liters per hour).
This system utilizes the innovative patented technology of double pass through the reverse osmosis membrane for optimal performance.
The central module of the Playgreen 6 has a capacity of 1.6 gallons per hour (6 liters per hour) and includes an internal system of valves, allowing for the efficient maintenance of two independent humidification zones. Compact in size, this system is perfect for two groups of rooms with a combined volume of up to 30,000 cubic feet. The Playgreen 6 with PG6UV comes equipped with a comprehensive 5 + 2 (optional) stage filtration system, which includes continuous 2-stage UV water sterilization. Humidistats are strategically installed within each humidification zone to control the precise operation of the nozzles.
The equipment is produced in branded aluminum cases with an original design. All rights reserved.
Playgreen 12, a high capacity system with a 2-zone capability and a PG12UV unit, delivering an impressive throughput of 3.2 gallons per hour (12 liters per hour).
Similar to its predecessor, this system also utilizes the patented double pass technology through the reverse osmosis membrane for enhanced efficiency.
The central module of the Playgreen 12 boasts a capacity of 3.2 gallons per hour (12 liters per hour) and features an internal system of valves that can effectively maintain two independent humidification zones. Furthermore, this system requires the addition of a high pressure unit and optional filter and softener units, each carefully selected to match the quality of the supplied tap water. All water processed by the Playgreen 12 undergoes internal 2-stage UV treatment, ensuring its purity. With its outstanding performance, this system is capable of servicing two groups of rooms with a combined volume of up to 60,000 cubic feet. Humidistats installed within each humidification zone are responsible for precise control of the nozzles' operation.

The central module of the Manitoba 12 possesses a capacity of 3.2 gallons per hour (12 liters per hour) and supports up to 10 independent humidification zones (which can be expanded up to 20 zones through cascading). Similar to the Playgreen 12, this system requires the addition of a high pressure unit and optional filter and softener units, selected to match the quality of the tap water supply. All water processed by the Manitoba 12 undergoes internal 2-stage UV treatment to ensure its quality. Capable of servicing a group of rooms with a total volume of up to 60,000 cubic feet, this system is exceptionally effective. Humidistats, along with control nozzles, create a unique relative humidity level specific to each room.
Superior 18, a premium high capacity system boasting S18UV units with a throughput of 4.8 gallons per hour (18 liters per hour)
This system utilizes a 2-stage reverse osmosis process and features the SEPAMED pump for enhanced performance.

The central module's capacity is 4.8 GPH (18 LPH). The module supports up to 10 (20 cascaded) independent humidification zones. In addition to the central module, the ultra-carbon filter and the softener (optional) must be added. Superior 18 system provides the deepest possible water treatment thanks to 2-stage reverse osmosis and continuous extensive sterilization of water by ultraviolet light. Superior 18 system has high performance and may operate with a group of rooms with the total volume up to 90,000 ft3. Humidistats are installed in rooms and control nozzles maintaining in each separate zone its own humidity level.

All equipment within these systems is equipped with a leakage protection system and sensors for malfunction and water shutdown detection. In the event of malfunction or breakdown, all separate components of the system can be easily disconnected for servicing. The compact, self-contained, and automated nature of these modules ensures convenience and ease of use. The frequency of maintenance depends on the quality and quantity of water used but is typically carried out once a year (once every 2-3 years for the Superior 18). Rest assured, all equipment is certified and extensively tested to meet the required technical specifications after assembly.
